<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2nd Man Dies After Pool Hall Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A second man died Thursday of injuries caused
by a sport utility vehicle that plowed into a crowded pool hall
near the UCLA campus on Wednesday. The 39-year-old driver remained
in critical condition with self-inflicted wounds from trying to
slit his throat with a piece of glass after the crash, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Detectives had not determined whether Wednesday's collision was
accidental or deliberate, Officer Dan Kemble said Thursday. He said
a preliminary evaluation indicated the driver was not under the
influence of drugs or alcohol.
</P>
<P>
   Noah Baum, 34, of West Hollywood, was killed when the vehicle
jumped a curb and smashed into the front section of Q's Billiard
Club, coming to rest inside the front bar in a hail of shattered
glass and splintered wood. A 26-year-old man hit during the crash
died Thursday at UCLA Medical Center, hospital spokesman Alan
Eyerly said. His name was not released.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
