<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 02:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-GSA Chief Denies Talking To Gore  </HEADLINE>
By PETE YOST
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The former head of the General Services
Administration says he never talked to Vice President Al Gore or
anyone else in the Clinton administration about a proposed $400
million federal lease for a Democratic fund-raiser and long-time
friend of Gore.
</P>
<P>
   Ex-GSA administrator Roger Johnson made the comments Thursday
night in response to public disclosure of a memo suggesting that
''Gore has called or is ready to call'' Johnson in an attempt to
help Tennessee developer Franklin Haney on a planned building
called the Portals. Gore denies intervening on the Portals project.
</P>
<P>
   Justice Department investigators got the undated, unsigned and
unaddressed memo pursuant to a grand jury subpoena, but have been
unable to learn who wrote the three-paragraph document, U.S. Rep.
Thomas Bliley, R-Va., revealed in a letter to Attorney General
Janet Reno.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson said government investigators questioned him over a year
ago about the Portals.
</P>
<P>
   ''They were asking me was there any pressure on me from the
administration to do anything'' for ''a developer, I think it was
one of the vice president's people'' and ''my answer 'was
absolutely not,''' said Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson emphasized that he didn't have a conversation about the
Portals with the vice president ''or anybody else in the
administration'' about the Portals. ... That's the bottom line.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson's chief of staff, Barbara Silbey, met regarding the
Portals in Johnson's office with long-time Gore fund-raiser Peter
Knight, to whom Haney paid $1 million for work on that and other
real estate deals.
</P>
<P>
   ''There was a meeting between GSA and Mr. Haney,'' Silbey said
in a statement. ''There were lawyers present and the meeting was
for the entirely legitimate purpose of discussing Mr. Haney's plans
in connection with the Portals. Every aspect of government
contracting law was complied with to the fullest.''
</P>
<P>
   The memo suggested a strategy for pushing the Portals deal that
included contacting Silbey.
</P>
<P>
   ''Let her know that you are also a major player in the
fund-raising arena'' and ''that Gore has called or is ready to call
Johnson and that he appreciates'' Silbey's ''help in resolving the
issue,'' the memo said.
</P>
<P>
   Republicans on the House committee said lease changes obtained
by Haney cost taxpayers millions of dollars in rent for months
before government workers moved into the newly constructed
building. Besides the money to Knight, Haney also paid $1.8 million
in less than a year to former Sen. James Sasser for help on the
Portals and other real estate projects.
</P>
<P>
   Bliley is seeking a criminal investigation into why the memo
which identifies Gore by name three times wasn't turned over to the
House Commerce subcommittee on oversight and investigations in its
yearlong probe of the Portals deal in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   The memo states: ''Whomever Gore designates to call Roger should
also call the Deputy Administrator and PBS Commissioner'' at GSA.
''They need strokes too. The problem is that they don't know anyone
anywhere. So a stroke is a little more difficult. This can be
played by ear.''
</P>
<P>
   In his letter, Bliley said that ''of the 20 or so relevant
people the FBI interviewed on this subject (including Vice
President Gore), not one of them could offer any clues'' as to who
wrote the document.
</P>
<P>
   ''Apparently no one -- even including the person who produced it
to DOJ -- had ever seen this document before, no one had drafted it,
and no one knew who had drafted it,'' Bliley's letter added.
</P>
<P>
   Due to grand jury secrecy rules, the Justice Department has
declined to tell Congress who supplied the memo to prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
   Justice Department spokesman Myron Marlin said that ''we've been
having discussions with the committee about this matter and are
reviewing'' Bliley's letter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-02-00 0204 </TRAILER>
