<HEADLINE> NFL To Experiment With 'HelmetCams'  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The NFL plans to let broadcasters put miniature
cameras inside helmets and wire its players with microphones during
exhibition games.
</P>
<P>
   ''The idea is to experiment in the preseason and see how it
works,'' NFL spokesman Greg Aiello told The New York Times on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper said officials might also be outfitted with
miniature cameras.
</P>
<P>
   ABC, CBS, Fox and ESPN broadcast NFL games.
</P>
