<HEADLINE> Stock Prices Up in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were sharply higher in Friday's
early trading.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 134 points in the early
going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange held a
nearly 4-1 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index was ahead 150 points and the Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index was up 20 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Labor Department reported that the jobless rate rose
two-tenths of a percent in May to 4.1 percent. And payrolls grew by
just 231,000.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices soared on the news, as have the major stock market
averages in Europe.
</P>
<P>
   Investors have been looking for signs that the Federal Reserve's
rate hikes are having the desired effect of slowing the economy to
a more sustainable pace of growth.
</P>
