<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Heart Failure Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Associated Press on May 30 misidentified a
physician experimenting with a new treatment for heart failure. Dr.
Steven Higgins of Scripps Memorial Hospital in San Diego has
implanted 60 Americans with the experimental ''ventricular
resynchronizer.'' He was erroneously identified as Dr. Scott
Higgins.
</P>
