<HEADLINE> Tom Cruise Sings Karaoke  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) -- Tom Cruise knows his limits, but he sang
in public anyway Friday, bowing to the pressures of this
karaoke-mad island.
</P>
<P>
   Cruise was goaded into the performance by a reporter at a news
conference where the actor promoted ''Mission: Impossible 2.''
</P>
<P>
   Cruise chose the last song he sang on film: the Righteous
Brothers hit ''You've Lost That Loving Feeling,'' from 1986's ''Top
Gun.''
</P>
<P>
   ''You never close your eyes anymore when I kiss your lips, and
there's no tenderness,'' he sang in a low, hesitant voice.
</P>
<P>
   He didn't finish the line.
</P>
<P>
   ''I couldn't sing then, and I can't sing now,'' Cruise said.
</P>
</TEXT>
