<HEADLINE> Selena Statue Prompts Outpouring  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- City cleanup crews can hardly keep
up with the graffiti and messages of love and grief left at a
statue of Selena, the Grammy-winning Tejano singer slain in 1995.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's an emotional message center that we are unable to deal
with,'' said businessman Dusty Durrill. A foundation named for his
daughter paid for the memorial.
</P>
<P>
   City workers have to clean up the bronze statue at least once a
week. The city is considering several ideas, including surrounding
the statue with a galvanized steel cage.
</P>
<P>
   The 23-year-old singer was shot by Yolanda Saldivar, who ran
Selena's clothing business. Saldivar was convicted of murder and is
serving a life sentence.
</P>
</TEXT>
