<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prince to Celebrate Name Switch  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- The artist formerly known as an
unpronounceable symbol is holding a weeklong party to celebrate his
switch back to the name Prince.
</P>
<P>
   The party begins Wednesday at his Paisley Park studio in
Chanhassen, and he will perform June 13 in Minneapolis.
</P>
<P>
   ''Paisley Park is pretty much representative of everything I am
musically,'' he told KMSP-TV on Thursday. ''I love Minnesota. I've
lived here all my life, and I plan to stay.''
</P>
<P>
   Prince said he kept his local studio so that he wouldn't have to
run back and forth to Los Angeles or New York.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've found that you tend to reflect whatever it is that's
around you,'' he said. ''I wanted peace around me, so I stayed here
so I could reflect peace. I needed a place like this to create.''
</P>
</TEXT>
