<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 16:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Meets With Kohl  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BERLIN (AP) -- In a show of loyalty for an old pal, President
Clinton met Friday evening with former German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl, whose legacy was recently tarnished by a campaign financing
scandal.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is the first foreign leader to meet with Kohl since the
former chancellor's reputation was shattered following his
admission last December of accepting illegal campaign contributions
while in office.
</P>
<P>
   The two last met in April 1999 in Washington where Clinton
awarded Kohl the Presidential Medal of Freedom, the United States'
highest civilian award, saluting his 16 years as German chancellor.
</P>
<P>
   Kohl was in the Clinton's hotel for about an hour before
leaving, brushing past reporters saying only, ''It was a meeting
among friends.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
