<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shelton To Visit S. Arabia, Kuwait  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Gen. Henry H. Shelton, chairman of the Joint
Chiefs of Staff, will leave Sunday on a Persian Gulf trip to visit
American troops and military leaders in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
   In Saudi Arabia on Tuesday Shelton will participate in a
ceremony marking the installation of a new commander of the U.S.
Military Training Mission, and he will hold talks with Gen. Saleh
bin Ali bin Al-Muhayya, chief of the Saudi General Staff.
</P>
<P>
   Shelton also will visit U.S. troops at Prince Sultan Air Base,
which houses U.S. forces that help enforce the ''no fly'' zone over
southern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday Shelton will meet with the Kuwaiti minister of
defense, Sheik Salem Al Sabah and then visit U.S. troops based in
Kuwait. Shelton will attend NATO meetings in Brussels, Belgium, on
Thursday and Friday and then return to Washington.
</P>
</TEXT>
