<HEADLINE> Three dead in I-95 crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   DARIEN, Conn. (AP) -- Three people died in a fiery crash on
Interstate 95 that shut down the highway for several hours Friday
morning.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred just before 6 a.m. and involved a
tractor-trailer rig and two other vehicles, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said a tractor trailer lost control, collided with two
cars and forced them into the center barrier. Alll three vehicles
burst into flames.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses and emergency crews tried to free three people trapped
inside one of the burning cars. Those three people died.
</P>
<P>
   Two people in the other passenger vehicle and the truck driver
were treated at Norwalk Hospital for minor injuries, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident between exit 9 and 10 shut down the highway
northbound at that point, snarling traffic for miles.
</P>
<P>
   Police had not released the names of the dead Friday evening.
</P>
