<HEADLINE> Chargers Re-Sign Kenny Bynum  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Running back Kenny Bynum, a restricted free
agent, signed a one-year contract Friday to remain with the San
Diego Chargers.
</P>
<P>
   Bynum had a team-high 1,277 total yards last season, from a
team-best 781 kickoff return yards, 287 rushing (second on the
team), and 209 receiving. He added seven tackles on special teams
as one of San Diego's top cover men.
</P>
<P>
   Bynum, a fifth-round draft pick in 1997, has been the Chargers'
leading kickoff returner the past three seasons.
