<HEADLINE> Piazza Examined Before Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Mets catcher Mike Piazza went to a Manhattan
hospital for a CAT scan before Friday's game against the Tampa Bay
Devil Rays, then returned to the ballpark with medical clearance to
play.
</P>
<P>
   Piazza was struck in the head two days earlier by the bat of the
Dodgers' Gary Sheffield and was sent to the hospital after
complaining of feeling ''sluggish''.
</P>
<P>
   Piazza was hit by on Sheffield's follow-through Wednesday night
at Los Angeles, taking a stitch in the head to stop bleeding and
was reported to have a slight concussion. He had been expected to
play Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Piazza, hitting .372 with 14 homers and 36 RBIs in 45 games, was
sent to the Hospital of Special Surgery in Manhattan for the test.
</P>
