<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 21:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expos Honoring Hockey Great  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- The Montreal Expos will wear a black No. 9 on
their home and away jerseys for the rest of the 2000 season in
memory of late Montreal Canadiens hockey great Maurice ''Rocket''
Richard.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first time in major league history that an athlete
from another sport had been so honored. The Expos, who got approval
from the commissioner's office for the tribute, wore the number for
the first time during Friday night's game against Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   Richard, the first player in NHL history to score 50 goals in a
season and 500 career goals, died Saturday. He was accorded a state
funeral Wednesday, which was broadcast live across Canada.
</P>
<P>
   A moment of silence was observed prior to Friday night's game
against the Orioles.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-02-00 2104 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000602.0156 </DOCNO>
