<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-02 21:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rams Reach Deal With Allen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Cornerback Taje Allen, a restricted free agent,
signed a one-year, $472,000 deal Friday to stay with the St. Louis
Rams.
</P>
<P>
   Allen had two regular-season interceptions for the Super Bowl
champions a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   The Rams also re-signed three exclusive rights free agents to
one-year contracts. They are wide receiver Tony Horne ($358,000),
defensive tackle Nate Hobgood-Chittick ($358,000), and running back
Justin Watson ($275,000).
</P>
<P>
   Horne led the Rams in kickoff returns last season, averaging
29.7 yards and scoring two touchdowns.
</P>
