</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- An ex-convict was acquitted today of conspiring to
kidnap atheist Madalyn Murray O'Hair and her family but found guilty of
extorting money from them. O'Hair, her son Jon Garth Murray and granddaughter
Robin Murray O'Hair disappeared in 1995 along with $500,000 in gold coins.
Authorities believe they were killed and dismembered, though their bodies were
never found. Gary Paul Karr, 52, convicted on four counts involving extortion
but acquitted on a fifth count, conspiracy to kidnap, faces life in prison under
the so-called federal three strikes law because of his prior convictions.
Sentencing was set for Aug. 4.
</P>
