nine American men who started the tennis tournament were gone -- from Pete
Sampras in the first round to defending champion Andre Agassi in the second to
Michael Chang in the third. Chang's exit today marked the earliest wipeout of
American men in 33 years of Grand Slam play. He lost to 1997 champion Gustavo
Kuerten in a 6-3, 6-7 (9), 6-1, 6-4 defeat.
</P>
