<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers' Mateo Injured  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Texas center fielder Ruben Mateo, one of
the American League's top rookies, was carried off the field on a
cart Friday night after he tripped over first base while trying to
beat out a grounder.
</P>
<P>
   When Arizona second baseman Craig Counsell briefly bobbled the
grounder, Mateo made an extra effort to get to the base. His right
foot landed awkwardly on a corner of the bag and he went tumbling
to the ground.
</P>
<P>
   Mateo, who was out on the play that ended the seventh inning,
was on the field for about 10 minutes before he was put on a
stretcher and lifted onto the cart after his right leg was
stabilized.
</P>
<P>
   Texas said the injury appeared to be to the upper right leg or
right knee. Mateo was taken to a Fort Worth hospital for X-rays and
evaluation.
</P>
<P>
   Mateo, who has started 52 of the Rangers' 53 games in center
field, is hitting .291 with seven home runs and 19 RBIs. He leads
AL rookies in average, multihit games (18), hits (60), runs (32)
and total bases (92), while ranking second among first-year players
in stolen bases (s) and doubles (11).
</P>
</TEXT>
