<HEADLINE> El Salvador Police: Soldier Kills 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) -- A drunken policeman opened fire
on a military patrol with an automatic rifle Friday, killing seven
people and injuring two, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Police and soldiers were on a joint patrol near the village of
El Tablon, about 120 miles east of the capital, when one of the
police officers opened fire, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Five soldiers and two bystanders, both women, were killed. A
policeman and a seven-month-old baby were wounded.
</P>
<P>
   Military troops assisted by police helicopters arrested police
officer Luis Navarrette in connection with the attack.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said they didn't know of a motive for the shooting.
</P>
</TEXT>
